==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chaldean
<hw>Chal*de"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Chaldaeus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Chaldea.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A native or inhabitant of
Chaldea.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A learned man, esp. an astrologer; --
so called among the Eastern nations, because astrology and the kindred
arts were much cultivated by the Chaldeans.</def> <sd>(c)</sd>
<def>Nestorian.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chaldee</ent>⟦br⟧
